<div class="manual-text">
<section class="Sh">
<h1 class="Sh" id="NAME"><a class="permalink" href="#NAME">NAME</a></h1>
<code class="Nm">flashctl</code> &#x2014;
<div class="Nd">a program to manipulate flash devices</div>
</section>
<section class="Sh">
<h1 class="Sh" id="SYNOPSIS"><a class="permalink" href="#SYNOPSIS">SYNOPSIS</a></h1>
<table class="Nm">
  <tr>
    <td><code class="Nm">flashctl</code></td>
    <td><var class="Ar">device</var> <var class="Ar">command</var>
      [<var class="Ar">arg</var> [...]]</td>
  </tr>
</table>
</section>
<section class="Sh">
<h1 class="Sh" id="DESCRIPTION"><a class="permalink" href="#DESCRIPTION">DESCRIPTION</a></h1>
<code class="Nm">flashctl</code> could be used to invoke low level operations
  specific to flash devices. It is used by specifying a device to manipulate,
  the command to perform, and any arguments the command may require.
</section>
<section class="Sh">
<h1 class="Sh" id="DEVICE_COMMANDS"><a class="permalink" href="#DEVICE_COMMANDS">DEVICE
  COMMANDS</a></h1>
The following commands may be used on flash devices:
<dl class="Bl-tag">
  <dt><a class="permalink" href="#badblocks"><code class="Cm" id="badblocks">badblocks</code></a></dt>
  <dd>List the bad blocks on the device.</dd>
  <dt><a class="permalink" href="#erase"><code class="Cm" id="erase">erase</code></a>
    <var class="Ar">offset</var> <var class="Ar">size</var></dt>
  <dd>Erase <var class="Ar">size</var> amount of flash memory from
      <var class="Ar">offset</var>. Size could be <var class="Ar">all</var>,
      which means the rest of the flash after <var class="Ar">offset</var> will
      be erased.</dd>
  <dt><a class="permalink" href="#identify"><code class="Cm" id="identify">identify</code></a></dt>
  <dd>Identify the specified device, displaying the device's vendor, product
      strings, and the device's capabilities.</dd>
  <dt><a class="permalink" href="#markbad"><code class="Cm" id="markbad">markbad</code></a>
    <var class="Ar">offset</var></dt>
  <dd>Mark the block given by its <var class="Ar">offset</var> as bad.</dd>
</dl>
</section>
